messages.title: FOR ENOUGH STAFF TO KEEP PATIENTS SAFE
messages.content: Under the Tories, there are now over 1 million people who wait over 4 hours in A&E. Labour created the NHS and will always save it.

messages.title: AND TO END HOSPITAL CLOSURES
messages.content: Tory cuts have led to over 14,000 hospital beds being cut since 2010 and A&E waiting lists are at their highest level in a decade.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Addressing the issues of staff shortages, long waiting times in A&E, and hospital bed cuts with a commitment to save the NHS.

issues.health: Under the Tories, there are now over 1 million people who wait over 4 hours in A&E. Tory cuts have led to over 14,000 hospital beds being cut since 2010 and A&E waiting lists are at their highest level in a decade.

images.caption: Labour's commitment to address the healthcare crisis, end hospital closures, and reduce A&E waiting times.
